Graphite producer and battery anode material developer Volt Resources refers to the announcement titled “Volt Joins Gigafactory Development in United States” dated 10 February 2022 and provides the following further information. Energy Supply Developers LLC (ESD) is developing a unique integrated LIB facility with planned capacity of up to 50 gigawatt-hours (Gigafactory). The Gigafactory facilities will be developed by ESD to incorporate battery materials suppliers, LIB cell manufacturer(s), R&D facilities and associated utilities and infrastructure. RELATED:AVZ Minerals completes US$240 million cornerstone investmentFinal high-grade infill drilling results received for Ewoyaa lithium projectAtlantic Lithium: West Africa’s first lithium production on the horizon ESD has entered into a number of LOI’s and is having further discussions with battery materials suppliers, cell manufacturers, property and construction groups and expects to make further announcements in relation to Gigafactory participants in the near future. Negotiations with US Midwest states for the ESD Gigafactory site location are nearly finalized. Once the site is selected, ESD will officially announce its development plans, board and management team and Gigafactory participants through a media and public relations launch including website and other traditional and social media platforms. ESD has selected Volt to be the coated spheroinised purified graphite (CSPG) supplier for its Gigafactory that is expected to commence operations in 2025. ESD and Volt have executed a non-binding LOI which contemplates entering into a binding lease agreement covering the area within the integrated Gigafactory facility within which Volt will install its CSPG processing equipment.